<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<RelativeLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:background="@drawable/litba"
    android:paddingBottom="@dimen/activity_vertical_margin"
    android:paddingLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
    android:paddingRight="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
    android:paddingTop="@dimen/activity_vertical_margin"
    tools:context="com.boombar.drjoshi.fragment.Litrary.Quiz">
    <ScrollView
        android:layout_width="fill_parent"
        android:layout_height="fill_parent">
        <LinearLayout
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:orientation="vertical">
            <Button
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="33dp"
                android:text="Extempore"
                android:layout_marginTop="20dp"
                android:textSize="15dp"
                android:gravity="center"
                android:textStyle="bold"
                android:typeface="monospace"
                android:textColor="#ffff"
                android:background="#7d00ff6a"/>
            <Button
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="23dp"
                android:text="Rules and Guidelines"
                android:layout_marginTop="20dp"
                android:textSize="15dp"
                android:gravity="center"
                android:textStyle="bold"
                android:typeface="monospace"
                android:textColor="#ffff"
                android:background="#7300ffea"/>
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="20dp"
                android:text="
The quiz will be conducted in 5 rounds to test the overall knowledge of the participating team. Each team will have 2 participants. After each round the team with lowest score will be eliminated. The details of respective rounds are:-\n
1. Round 1 (Serious/Joking)\n
In this round a fact/statement will be flashed on the screen before the teams and they have to give answer in only two words i.e. Serious or Joking.\n
2. Round 2 (Know your State)\n
In this round questions related to Uttarakhand will be asked and the questions will cover all the important information regarding the state that a learned person must know.\n
3. Round 3 (Hit – or – Miss)\n
As the name suggests in this round, random questions of general knowledge will be asked which have to be answered using only one word.\n
4. Round 4 ( Phehchan kaun?)\n
This is an audio- visual round. Sorry, we can’t get into more details.\n
5. Round 5(Grand finale)\n
This is a rapid fire round in which the final three teams will have to choose among the following categories:\n
History, Geography, Politics, Holly-Bolly, Sports\n
The team with highest score in round 4 will be the first one to choose the category.\n A maximum of 10 questions will be asked per team in this round."
                android:textSize="16dp"
                android:typeface="monospace"
                android:textColor="#000"
                android:gravity="center"
                />
            <Button
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="23dp"
                android:text="Points in GOONJ:"
                android:layout_marginTop="20dp"
                android:textSize="15dp"
                android:gravity="center"
                android:textStyle="bold"
                android:typeface="monospace"
                android:textColor="#ffff"
                android:background="#8df99900"/>
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:text="
1. 100\n
2. 75\n
3. 50"
                android:textSize="16dp"
                android:typeface="monospace"
                android:textColor="#000"
                android:gravity="center"
                />
        </LinearLayout>
    </ScrollView>
</RelativeLayout>
